{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"GLHB2UVCnE6nVxFI7vDeE","title":"Empirical Study","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"inflation-forecasting":{"type":"header","text":"Inflation Forecasting","value":"inflation-forecasting","line":14,"column":0},"gdp-forecasting":{"type":"header","text":"GDP forecasting","value":"gdp-forecasting","line":19,"column":0},"unemployment-forecasting":{"type":"header","text":"Unemployment forecasting","value":"unemployment-forecasting","line":22,"column":0}},"fname":"CWF.empirical","updated":1636331440143,"created":1636095716715,"parent":"MsmFdXyWfizd5g8GGcObD","children":["6jScjSKL9hxSIPTbWMgAH"],"data":{},"contentHash":"4ddc68b411fab7bb61f300f96eab7e99","custom":{}},"body":"<p>Many different empirical studies are possible, given the general nature of the methodology.</p>\n<p>For now, focus on the task of inflation forecasting, as this is topical and popular, and there exists a large literature for this. It is also not as controversial to deem forecastable, unlike say, financial data.</p>\n<p>There are broadly three macroeconomic indicators that economists tend to care about, and these are all closely related to the functions of a central bank. They are inflation, GDP (economic output) and unemployment (\"efficiency\" of economic output).</p>\n<h2 id=\"inflation-forecasting\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#inflation-forecasting\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Inflation Forecasting</h2>\n<p>We consider three different measures of inflation: the personal consumption expenditures (PCE) deflator, the CPI, and core CPI (CPI less food). Inflation rates are computed via <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>π</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>l</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>g</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>π</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>−</mo><msub><mi>π</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\pi_t = log(\\pi_t - \\pi_{t-1})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03588em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03588em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.301108em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03588em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.208331em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> (as opposed to the suggested transformation of 2nd log differences in Stock and Watson). </p>\n<h2 id=\"gdp-forecasting\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#gdp-forecasting\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>GDP forecasting</h2>\n<p>It has been noted that unlike inflation forecasting, model based GDP forecasting does much better than most subjective forecasts. </p>\n<h2 id=\"unemployment-forecasting\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#unemployment-forecasting\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Unemployment forecasting</h2>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"children\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#children\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Children</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/6jScjSKL9hxSIPTbWMgAH\">Inflation Forecasting Review</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":451},"end":{"line":12,"column":12,"offset":462},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":464},"end":{"line":14,"column":12,"offset":475},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Meeting"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"TODO","alias":"TODO","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":477},"end":{"line":16,"column":9,"offset":485},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"TODO"}},{"type":"linkCandidate","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Dendron has incredibly powerful search functionality due to good indexing, even outside of working in raw .md files. Simply use the search bar at the top of the website to find something.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":246},"end":{"line":8,"column":188,"offset":433},"indent":[]},"to":{"fname":"Dendron","vaultName":"vault"}}],"anchors":{"quick-links":{"type":"header","text":"Quick Links","value":"quick-links","line":17,"column":0},"to-do-list":{"type":"header","text":"To do List","value":"to-do-list","line":25,"column":0}},"fname":"root","updated":1636683885086,"created":1595961348801,"parent":null,"children":["CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","9s2d4L1UHWFWCdtORYT2Q","AiXOWFsdvi3BPZxcUMjIi","MXHvc8bQbNRRVCB0UogRy","MsmFdXyWfizd5g8GGcObD","jtZSk246bVVDfJy6cdpS1","2qGHFR7CcKOE0Meu7UU6D","T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","qGmGYptDKW2WLwlsu2xJw","GvwoAWaYZxq1czYi3t3k4","ZIDZSAYP9a9L7jYhVMgcz","WOnXV41UlGcOQzEoTZzJU","fhf7Gdr3mhOUG1mU5twC6","AOvKFmg0tBcGmUASXaALX","qDVp6IFHf6FiUdSgxwZMA","fHzGITjWkNNkiwsQpdex4","umGHrdI4OaLoU8OOAOdkL","aQw5xJBpqunSJYCfXXAls","y0rpX1u3Lz3vpUFro9TcW","AuDqSlWn0PlsSo8JdLgrR","ElqQePaEuSSz7pSeO1gNc","0R61RLuT7e3hswR2v6o0w","FNflnQbSXuMwTtni2C8is","BMClpTRP3V8ITqM7R4kh0"],"data":{},"contentHash":"d7de26282e04813f39247a66c191dd07","custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"body":"\nWelcome to my website!\n\nThis website has been built using Dendron, and each topic has been collated into collapsible sections on the left hand side. Below is a high level overview showing how each section is connected for ease of navigation.\n\n\n\nDendron has incredibly powerful search functionality due to good indexing, even outside of working in raw .md files. Simply use the search bar at the top of the website to find something.\n\n## Quick Links\n\n[[roadmap]]\n\n[[Meeting]]\n\n[[TODO]]\n\n## To do List\n\nType up Bai and Ng assumptions\n\nInvestigate Bates et al Assumptions\n\nInvestigate consistency of using an estimated break point in conjunction with BNIC\nThis seems to be consistent using k_tilde that itself may be Op(1)\n\nFix up BP test for better interface (low priority)\n\nImplement simulated Andrews exp and mean Wald/LM tests\n\n- look into RSpectra package (supposedly faster eigen)\n- not sure whether to rename this to SFM or not (lots of legacy code that needs to be changed)\n\nData\nFix and clean data for \n- AUMD (on hold, need to find date index)\n- FREDQD\n- CANMD (should be straightforward)\n- CANQD\n- UKMD (should be straightforward)\n\nInvestigate further sources of time series that could be used during COVID\n\nImplement truly dynamic factor models (Forni) using Dynamic PCA\n- BIG task\n- read into dynamic PCA\n- read into testing no. of dynamic factors\n- do not believe there is a literature focusing on breaks in the dynamic setup\n- implement dynamic PCA\n- implement testing no of factors, (look into ICshocks functions and make this interface better)\n- implement testing no of factors using AW test\n\nImplement BKW standard test (non sequential)\n\nFix up BKW test\n- implement a general plot method which plots *something* on the y axis, but most importantly, date on the x axis with estimated break dates, and each partition labelled with the no. of factors as determined by some consistent estimator\n\nFix up BE test\n- so that there is a consistent interface for accessing this\n\n\n\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":3,"useFMTitle":false,"useNoteTitleForLink":true,"noLegacyNoteRef":true,"mermaid":true,"useKatex":true,"usePrettyRefs":true,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"site":{"copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"siteRootDir":"docs","usePrettyRefs":true,"title":"Ze Yu","description":"Personal knowledge space","siteLastModified":true,"gh_edit_branch":"main","duplicateNoteBehavior":{"action":"useVault","payload":["vault"]},"siteUrl":"https://zeyuz35.github.io/","usePrettyLinks":true,"siteNotesDir":"notes","siteFaviconPath":"favicon.ico","gh_edit_link":true,"gh_edit_link_text":"Edit this page on GitHub","gh_root":"docs/","gh_edit_view_mode":"edit","writeStubs":true,"siteIndex":"root"},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":false,"leaveTrace":false}},"randomNote":{},"insertNote":{"initialValue":"templates"},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false}},"workspace":{"vaults":[{"fsPath":"vault"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily","name":"journal","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"childOfDomain"},"scratch":{"name":"scratch","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd.HHmmss","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain"},"graph":{"zoomSpeed":1},"enableAutoCreateOnDefi